the historic center of san francisco is the northeast quadrant of the city bordered by  market street  to the south it is here that the  financial district  is centered with  union square  the principal shopping and hotel district nearby  cable cars  carry residents and tourists alike up steep inclines to the summit of  nob hill  once the home of the citys business tycoons and down to  fishermans wharf  a tourist area featuring  dungeness crab  from a stillactive fishing industry also in this quadrant are  russian hill  a residential neighborhood with the famously crooked  lombard street   north beach  the citys version of  little italy  and  telegraph hill  which features  coit tower  nearby is san franciscos  chinatown  established in the 1860s the  tenderloin  is often seen as the  crime infested underbelly of the city
